==English==
===Etymology===
First as past participle "isolated", from Italian ''[[isolato]]'', "secluded", from ''[[isola]]'', "island", from Latin ''[[insula]]'', "island".
===Noun===
'''isolation'''
# The act of [[isolate|isolating]].
# The state of being [[isolate]]d, [[detached]], or [[separated]].
